# gatetool: manual example -- inputgate -> outputgate with no gatelength copies the
# input gate length unchanged (gatestretch defaults 0, mingatelength default 0.01 s
# = 1 tick < input length, no maxgatelength). tickrate 100.
#
# Input gate high t0..t19 (D = 20 ticks). Output tracks it exactly: high t0..t19,
# low from t20 (at the fall, D=20, stretch 0 -> length 20, off at tick 20).
tickrate 100
patch <<<
[gatetool]
    inputgate  = I1
    outputgate = O1
>>>
@0 set I1 1
@0 expect O1 1 tol 1e-4
@19 expect O1 1 tol 1e-4
@20 set I1 0
@20 expect O1 0 tol 1e-4
@25 expect O1 0 tol 1e-4
